article.headline: Belmont 79, North Florida 56
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Justin Hare scored 20 points and Belmont beat North Florida 79-56 on Saturday. Hare hit six of seven field goals, including two 3-pointers. Shane Dansby chipped in 13 points for Belmont, and Jordan Campbell had seven rebounds. The Bruins (17-8, 9-2 Atlantic Sun Conference) jumped to a 37-25 lead at the half. Chris Timberlake led the Ospreys (1-22, 0-11) with 18 points, while Tom Hammonds added 13 and Devon Jones 11. Jones also had six rebounds. Belmont made 24-of-32 free throws to 11-of-19 for North Florida.
